    <date day="12" month="November" year="2025"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>Prefix hijacking, i.e., unauthorized announcement of a prefix, has
   emerged as a major security threat in the Border Gateway Protocol
   (BGP), garnering widespread attention.  To migrate such attacks while
   supporting legitimate Multiple Origin AS (MOAS), higher requirements
   are placed on the route origin registry.  This document serves to
   outline the problem statement for current route origin registry.</t>
    </abstract>
